                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13447407" author="oliver.heger@t-online.de" created="Mon, 3 Sep 2012 21:41:10 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;A patch implementing the extraction of an MP3 file&apos;s duration. The patch uses two helper classes, &lt;tt&gt;MpegStream&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;TailStream&lt;/tt&gt; to iterate over all frames in the audio file. The functionality for interpreting frame headers has been moved into the &lt;tt&gt;MpegStream&lt;/tt&gt; class; this seemed to be clearer to me.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This patch also fixes the issue reported in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-990&quot; title=&quot;Mp3Parser extracts wrong number of channels&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-990&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-990&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13489746" author="oliver.heger@t-online.de" created="Fri, 2 Nov 2012 20:56:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached a new patch. I found a problem with handling of skipped bytes.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13570696" author="gagravarr" created="Mon, 4 Feb 2013 22:25:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Epic patch, thanks! I&apos;ve finally had a chance to review it, committed with a few small tweaks in r1442402.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13572814" author="oliver.heger@t-online.de" created="Wed, 6 Feb 2013 20:55:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for reviewing and committing!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In the meanwhile, I used this code in one of my projects and found one more issue related to the &lt;tt&gt;TailStream&lt;/tt&gt; class: Under certain circumstances the code can enter an endless loop. I am going to attach a patch with a corresponding fix soon.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13579487" author="oliver.heger@t-online.de" created="Fri, 15 Feb 2013 20:39:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As promised, this is an additional patch fixing a corner case in TailStream. It prevents that the MP3 parser can enter an endless loop when a skip operation is done at the end of the stream.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13684748" author="chrismattmann" created="Sun, 16 Jun 2013 20:14:35 +0100"  >&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;updated patch committed to 1.5 trunk in r1493574. Thanks Oliver!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="13756008" author="schmir" created="Mon, 2 Sep 2013 11:46:18 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the &quot;endloss loop fix&quot; would justify an 1.4.1 release. I&apos;ve just ran into that with tika 1.4.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
